casebody.data:
State of Nebraska, appellee, v. Calvin H. Dodd, appellant. Filed May 13, 1916. No. 18770. Per Curiam. Appeal from tbe district court for Dawes county: William BO. Westover, Judge. Albert W. Grites and Earl McDowell, for appellant. Justin E. Porter and Allen G. Fisher, contra.

Contempt: Review. A conviction under contempt proceedings can only Be reviewed in the supreme court By the filing of a petition in error as in a criminal case. Gandy v. State, 13 NeB. 445; Hanilca v. State, 87 NeB. 845.

Appeal dismissed.
